                            Dr. Robin is a professor in automation and intelligent systems, an IEEE Senior Member, and the head of the Cyber-Physical Systems Lab at NTNU, Ålesund, Norway. At the Department of ICT and Natural Sciences, Dr. Robin is an elected scientific staff member of the leader group and has headed the bachelor program in automation engineering since the summer of 2020. Dr. Robin's teaching activities include delivering engineering courses in the BSc Automation & Intelligent Systems and MSc Simulation & Visualization programs, as well as supervising BSc, MSc, PhD, and postdoc projects. Additionally, Dr. Robin develops and offers courses for lifelong learning.
                            Dr. Robin's research interests span the broad areas of cybernetics, artificial intelligence, neuroengineering, and education. As an affiliated scientist at NTNU AMOS (SFF), a Centre of Excellence funded by the Research Council of Norway, Dr. Robin is developing new methods for automated and autonomous systems at sea, including path planning and collision avoidance algorithms for ASVs. Dr. Robin is also investigating biomechanical robotics and machine learning for MR image segmentation for modeling and simulation of human joints and tissue. Dr. Robin's educational research focuses on student-active learning methodologies and digital tools for teaching, learning, and assessment.
