                        <p class="read-more" id="readMoreText26">
                            Dr. Shiju Sebastian stands as a prominent figure within the academic realm, holding the esteemed position of Associate Professor at Christ University, Bangalore. Renowned as one of India's distinguished Deemed Universities, Christ University embarked on a transformative journey to elevate Christ College to university status, and Dr. Sebastian was handpicked by the Board to lead this groundbreaking initiative. His unwavering commitment and pioneering spirit propelled him to spearhead this endeavor with unparalleled dedication. Dr. Sebastian played a the leading role in establishing crucial liaisons with key regulatory bodies in Indian higher education, including the UGC, AICTE, BCI, AIU, and NCTE. Member in the expert committee for the effective mitigation of human animal conflict in the State of Kerala. Additionally, he cultivated strong governmental relations with influential entities such as the Ministry of Human Resource Development and Bangalore University. Through these strategic partnerships and invaluable experiences, he solidified his reputation as a foremost expert in the field of academia and institutional development, in the nation of India.
